The paper presents a novel approach for using conditioning in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that can reduce runtime complexity and computation costs while maintaining or increasing accuracy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
